812016-03-30
MEMORANDUM OPINION AND ORDER re: 51 MOTION for Summary Judgment, filed by ADC Products (UK) Limited, 53 MOTION for Summary Judgment, filed by Peter J. Solomon Company, L.P., Peter J. Solomon Securities Company, L.L.C. Plaintiffs' motion for summary judgment is granted as to the issue of liability only. Defendant's motion for summary judgment is denied. Because there are material disputed issues of fact regarding the total amount of consideration that was paid in connection with the AZ transaction, and thus regarding the fee owed to Plaintiffs under the Agreement, the Court denies the Plaintiffs' summary judgment motion to the extent it seeks an award of damages. The parties are directed to use their best efforts to resolve the damages issue. The trial of this action will be limited to the issue of damages. The final pre-trial conference is hereby adjourned to June 16, 2016, at 10:00 a.m., and the parties are directed to consult and make submissions in advance of the conference as provided in the Pre-trial Scheduling Order (docket entry no. 14.) This Memorandum Opinion and Order resolves docket entry numbers 51 and 53. (As further set forth in this Order.) (Signed by Judge Laura Taylor Swain on 3/30/2016) (spo) (Entered: 03/30/2016)
